s among the\nparameters used by different methods to characterize an active region. For\nM-class flares and above, the set of methods tends towards a weakly positive\nskill score (as measured with several distinct metrics), with no participating\nmethod proving substantially better than climatological forecasts.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 22 Aug 2016 21:33:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-10-05"}
